50|$|In the United States, disclaimers on {{the sale}} of goods are covered by Article 2 of the Uniform Commercial Code, but details vary by state. Unless {{considered}} unconscionable, disclaimers are generally enforceable as part of a contract between knowledgeable parties of comparable bargaining power, but most states do not allow a party to limit their <b>liability</b> <b>for</b> gross <b>negligence.</b>|$|R
